  "prompt": "Can a person who is blind from birth dream?",
  "response": "Yes, a person who is blind from birth can dream. People who are blind from birth typically experience dreams that do not involve visual imagery, as they have no visual memories to draw from. Instead, their dreams may consist of sounds, smells, tactile sensations, emotions, and other non-visual elements. The content of their dreams is shaped by their experiences and perceptions in the waking world, which can provide a rich and vivid dream experience even without visual components.",
